==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ricinus
<hw>Ric"i*nus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the
castor-oil plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants of the
Spurge family, containing but one species (<spn>Ricinus communis</spn>),
the castor-oil plant. The fruit is three-celled, and contains three
large seeds from which castor oil is expressed. See <er>Palma
Christi</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rick</ent>⟦br⟧
